# Qwertystock sitemap crawler observability

- Treat Google/Bing/Yandex sitemap reads as a first-class SEO operations signal.
- Production must run `qwertystock-sitemap-access-watcher.service` to watch nginx
  access logs for `/sitemap.xml` and `/sitemaps/*.xml.gz`.
- The watcher must notify Telegram chat `-1003904421498`, topic id `514`.
- Notify immediately when a target crawler session starts reading sitemap files.
- Default Telegram notifications should be target-only:
  `Googlebot,Bingbot,YandexBot`. Use all-reader notifications only for temporary
  diagnostics.
- A crawler session is grouped by crawler family, IP, and User-Agent; sequential
  sitemap chunk downloads must update one Telegram message instead of sending a
  message per chunk.
- Track at least: crawler family, IP, User-Agent, first read time, last read
  time, request count, distinct sitemap files, latest path, status, and bytes.
- The daily QS indexing Telegram status must include a compact crawler summary
  for Googlebot, Bingbot, and YandexBot: either latest sitemap fetch stats or
  `ждём` when no fetch has been observed yet.
- The daily QS indexing Telegram status must include embedding health: indexed
  rows with embeddings, total qwertysearch rows, embedding coverage percent,
  missing-embedding queue, configured `--max-embedding-count`, limit utilization,
  free capacity, or overflow.
- Target crawler families are Googlebot/Google inspection agents,
  Bingbot/Microsoft indexing agents, and YandexBot/Yandex image/search agents.
- User-Agent detection is acceptable for operational reporting. Do not use it
  for security enforcement without reverse DNS or ASN verification.
- Use observed crawler fetch windows to tune the daily
  `qwertystock_daily_indexer.py` cron time. The sitemap build must finish before
  the recurring crawler fetch window with a safety buffer.
- Sitemap regeneration and crawler monitoring must be separate concerns:
  `qwertystock_daily_indexer.py` builds and reports sitemap state;
  `qwertystock_sitemap_access_watcher.py` reports external crawler reads.
- Do not treat sitemap reads as proof of item indexing. They only prove sitemap
  discovery/fetch. Continue validating Search Console, Bing Webmaster Tools,
  Yandex Webmaster, and sampled external-bot page checks.
- Do not submit the full catalog to IndexNow daily. IndexNow remains for
  changed/new/deleted URL deltas only.
